whether primary judge erred in finding that a decision by a deputy district registrar of the federal court of australia to reject a notice of appeal submitted for filing was not reviewable under s 35a(6) of the federal court act 1976 (cth)
held
exercise of power was not of the kind referred to in s 35a (1) and hence s 35a(6) did not apply.

citances.sentence: 2 The appellant appeals the decision of the primary judge delivered on 14 October 2009 in which the Court found that the appellant had failed to make out any ground for judicial review of the decision of the second respondent ('the Registrar') to reject the filing of the appellant's document entitled Notice of Appeal: see Satchithanantham v National Australia Bank Limited [2009] FCA 1171: (2009) 260 ALR 567.
